27/07/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- In a phone conversation on Thursday (July 26th), US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice congratulated new Albanian President Bamir Topi on his election victory.
She guaranteed US support for further consolidation of democratic processes and development of Albania.
Topi thanked Rice for the kind wishes, and stressed the importance of the US support for Albania's NATO bid.
Also Thursday, due to the ongoing energy crisis, the Albanian government reduced the working hours in the public administration to 8am-1pm.
The measure will go into effect Monday.
(Shekulli, Kohajone, Shqip, Tema - 27/07/07;
Top-Channel, Albanian president website -26/07/07)
